[b]Money Flow Delta Profile[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]

A directional volume/money flow profile. Every price row shows two bars anchored on the left, both extending to the right: a faint gray [b]reference bar[/b] (total flow at that level) and a colored [b]delta bar[/b] on top — green when buyers dominated, red when sellers dominated. The width of the delta bar relative to the gray bar shows conviction: a delta bar that nearly fills the reference bar means one side dominated decisively; a thin delta bar behind a wide gray bar means the level was heavily contested.

[b]How it works[/b]

[list]
[*]The lookback window (default 200 bars) is divided into price rows (default 25)
[*]Each bar's volume or money flow is distributed across the rows it overlaps, weighted by the overlap fraction
[*]Bull flow and bear flow are tracked separately using your choice of polarity method
[*]Delta at each row = bull flow − bear flow (positive = net buying, negative = net selling)
[*]Both the gray reference bar and the colored delta bar extend rightward from the same anchor — color (green/red) shows direction, width shows magnitude
[*]Reference bars are colored by node type (HVN / LVN / AVN — see below)
[/list]

[b]Key levels[/b]

[list]
[*][b]POC[/b] — Point of Control: the row with the highest total flow (yellow dashed line)
[*][b]Value Area[/b] — the price band containing a configurable % (default 70%) of total flow
[*][b]Delta POC[/b] — optional: the row with the strongest directional conviction (orange dotted line)
[/list]

[b]Node classification (HVN / LVN / AVN)[/b]

Reference bars are colored by their share of total flow relative to the row maximum:

[list]
[*][b]HVN[/b] (High Volume Node, warm orange) — rows with dense flow, > 80% of row maximum. These are areas of prior acceptance: price tends to slow or consolidate here.
[*][b]LVN[/b] (Low Volume Node, faded gray) — rows with thin flow, < 20% of row maximum. Price historically moved through quickly — potential acceleration zones or air pockets.
[*][b]AVN[/b] (Average Volume Node, neutral gray) — everything in between.
[/list]

[b]LVN Supply / Demand Zone Overlay[/b]

Adjacent Low Volume Node rows are automatically merged into zone boxes projected across the lookback period:

[list]
[*]Zones [b]above the POC[/b] are colored red — potential supply zones where price may face resistance
[*]Zones [b]below the POC[/b] are colored green — potential demand zones where price may find support
[*]Toggle on/off independently from the node coloring
[/list]

[b]Reading the profile[/b]

[list]
[*]Wide gray + wide green delta bar → high-volume demand zone, buyers dominated convincingly (HVN)
[*]Wide gray + wide red delta bar → high-volume supply zone, sellers dominated convincingly (HVN)
[*]Wide gray + short delta bar → contested level — heavy activity but balanced; expect choppy price action
[*]Narrow gray bar (LVN) → thin area — price historically moved through quickly; potential acceleration zone
[*]LVN zone above current price → air pocket supply; LVN zone below current price → air pocket demand
[/list]

[b]Options[/b]

[list]
[*]Source: Money Flow (volume × mid-price) or raw Volume
[*]Polarity: Bar Polarity (close vs open) or Close Location (proportional position in bar range)
[*]MF Price Mode: Row Mid / HL2 / Typical / Close — controls the price multiplier for Money Flow
[*]Recency Weighting: exponential decay so recent bars count more than older ones
[*]Value Area %: configurable (10–95%)
[*]HVN/LVN thresholds: configurable (default 80% / 20%)
[*]LVN Zone Overlay: toggle supply/demand zone boxes on/off
[/list]

